<p class="p">Relief-weighted hydrologic area (
 <italic class="italic">H</italic>) was used to capture the importance of valley-bottoms that provide landscape elements, such as riparian areas, across which aquatic and riparian-associated species and ecological processes can move and adapt to climate change [
 <xref rid="pone.0191468.ref030" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">30</xref>]. For each target pixel located on the hydrologic network within the moving window, we subtracted its elevation by the minimum elevation in the window, and then summed the relief values: 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0191468.e004" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0191468.e004.jpg" id="pone.0191468.e004g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M4" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">H</mi>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mstyle displaystyle="true" class="mstyle">
      <munderover class="munderover">
       <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">i</mi>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <mn class="mn">1</mn>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">n</mi>
       </mrow>
      </munderover>
     </mstyle>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">e</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">−</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">m</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">n</mi>
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">e</mi>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
